#loc_pathways

This is a repository for a project examining how locus of control changes over time across different college major pathways among students of color. The purpose of this project is to understand the role agency and feelings of control affect academic decision-making.

The project contains five folders: Archives, Code, Data, Procedure, and Reports. The Archives folder contains code for a boxplot of changes in locus of control by major pathway. The Code folder contains code for the simulated data and final project analyses. The Data folder contains a data dictionary, the simulated data file, and the real data. The reports folder contains the report code as an Rmd file, the project preregistration, project figures, as well as references.